   begin: 5283
   end: 6129
[ Representation learning has been successfully used to improve on the CoNLL shared task results  . Yang et al. (2015) report the smallest performance difference (5.5 points in F1) between in-domain and out-of-domain test data, leading to the best results to date on the CoNLL 2009 out-of-domain test. Their system learns common representations for in-domain and out-of-domain data based on deep belief networks.]
